		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I used to have a one-handed control adapter from Radio Shack where an NES controller slid in, and it had thumb and forefinger buttons for operating A and B.
<br />
<br />But accessibility is one of the reasons why I keep an open mind about new control schemes, be they for a video game or for a vehicle.

		

		</td>
