	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />That would be possible. Was it like you controlled the D-Pad with your thumb, and A/B/Start/Select with your other fingers on the back of the controller?
<br />
<br />And yeah, I try to consider other preferences for control schemes. In my game, I will have left-handed support for the controller (You can flip the NES controller upside down to control the D-Pad with your right hand, and the A/B buttons with your left). Though most left-handed people have learned to go against the grain with everything they do, it may be nice for some people.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
